esqlQuery.esql:
// Alert triggers when high latency is detected during AWS Bedrock AgentCore Gateway invocations.
//
// Gateway serves as a unified API endpoint that enables agents to securely connect to
// enterprise tools and resources. High latency can indicate network issues, slow
// downstream services, or resource constraints.
//
// Latency measures the average time elapsed between receiving the gateway request
// and returning the response, measured in milliseconds.
//
// The alert is grouped by cloud account, region, and resource to pinpoint the
// specific gateway experiencing high latency.
//
// To adjust sensitivity, change the threshold in the WHERE clause (default: 5000ms = 5 seconds).
// For more details, see: https://docs.aws.amazon.com/bedrock-agentcore/latest/devguide/observability-gateway-metrics.html

FROM metrics-aws_bedrock_agentcore.metrics-*
| WHERE aws.dimensions.Operation == "InvokeGateway"
| STATS avg_latency_ms = avg(aws.bedrock_agentcore.metrics.Latency.avg) BY cloud.account.id, cloud.region, aws.dimensions.Resource
| WHERE avg_latency_ms > 5000
